    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As a standard action, a drow noble can cause all creatures and objects in a 5-foot-radius burst to shed a pale glow. Creatures outlined by the limning light take a &ndash;20 penalty to Stealth checks and don&rsquo;t benefit from the concealment usually provided by darkness. If an affected creature is benefiting from an effect such as </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">invisibility</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, all others within line of sight of it become aware of its location (see page 260 of the </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Starfinder Core Rulebook</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">). This effect lasts for a number of minutes equal to the drow noble&rsquo;s CR (11 minutes for a drow noble arms dealer). This ability has a range of 100 feet.</span></p>"
